feed.title: Fisk Lab at URI
feed.subtitle: The Fisk Lab is a dry-lab at URI focused on using "basic science" methods from evolution, population genetics, genomics, and bioinformatics as tools for translational research. We also pusure Discipline-Based Education Research (DBER) for Computational Biology

entry.title: Fisk Lab Happenings Fall 2024
entry.content:
Post In Progress

This fall the Fisk Lab has been busy!

Welcome Amanda Shaughnessy to the lab!\

Coming up:

AAAI Machine Intellegence for Gloabl Health Equity - Invited Speaker
Brown Health (Lifespan) Research Day - Presenter \

URI CELS Graduate Seminar - Speaker \

Already Happened:

ASTRO24 - Education Session in DC
American Cancer Society Breakfast
AACR Special Conference on Pancreatic Cancer - Poster Presentation
Brown CCIDS - Seminar Speaker
Yale Metatasis of the Central Nervous System Workshop - Speaker
NMSU PACR/CS Seminar - Invited Seminar
PanCan Pokemon Stream Chairty Event - Organizer \
